# Laravel to Next.js (App Router) + TanStack Query Conversion Guide

## Overview

This guide covers migrating a Laravel monolith (Blade/Livewire/Inertia) to a **decoupled architecture**: Laravel becomes a **pure JSON API backend**, and Next.js (App Router) becomes the frontend. TanStack Query (formerly React Query) manages all client-side data fetching, caching, and mutations.

## Tech Stack

- **Laravel**: 12.x (API only — no Blade pages served to users)
- **Next.js**: 15.x (App Router — `app/` directory)
- **TanStack Query**: v5.x (`@tanstack/react-query`)
- **React**: 19.x
- **Laravel Sanctum**: for API authentication
- **Tailwind CSS**: 4.x

---

## Architecture Shift

```
BEFORE (Monolith)                   AFTER (Decoupled)
─────────────────────────────       ──────────────────────────────────
Browser → Laravel Routes            Browser → Next.js App Router
         → Blade/Livewire/Inertia            → React Server Components (RSC)
         → Database                           → fetch/TanStack Query
                                              → Laravel JSON API
                                              → Database
```

### Key Mental Shifts

| Laravel Monolith | Next.js + Laravel API |
|------------------|-----------------------|
| Routes render HTML | Routes return JSON (API resources) |
| Session auth (cookies) | Token auth (Sanctum Bearer / cookies) |
| Blade templates | React Server Components + Client Components |
| Livewire state | `useState` + TanStack Query |
| `@livewire('...')` | Next.js page + TanStack `useQuery()` |
| `Redirect::back()` | API returns JSON; frontend handles navigation |
| Flash messages | API response JSON `{ message: '...' }` |
| Laravel validation errors | API returns 422 with `errors` object |

