## Laravel API Layer

### Routes → API Resources

**Before (Blade/Livewire routes):**

```php
// routes/web.php
Route::get('/products', [ProductController::class, 'index'])->name('products.index');
Route::get('/products/{product}', [ProductController::class, 'show']);
Route::post('/products', [ProductController::class, 'store']);
```

**After (API routes):**

```php
// routes/api.php
Route::middleware('auth:sanctum')->group(function () {
    Route::apiResource('products', ProductController::class);
});
```

> `apiResource` creates GET/POST/PUT/DELETE routes without Blade-only routes (create/edit).

---

### Controllers → Return JSON

**Before (Inertia/Blade controller):**

```php
public function index(): \Inertia\Response
{
    return Inertia::render('Products/Index', [
        'products' => Product::all(),
    ]);
}
```

**After (API controller):**

```php
use App\Http\Resources\ProductResource;

public function index(): \Illuminate\Http\Resources\Json\AnonymousResourceCollection
{
    return ProductResource::collection(Product::paginate(20));
}

public function show(Product $product): ProductResource
{
    return new ProductResource($product);
}

public function store(Request $request): ProductResource
{
    $data    = $request->validate(['name' => 'required|string', 'price' => 'required|numeric']);
    $product = Product::create($data);
    return new ProductResource($product);
}
```

---

### API Resources (Shape the JSON)

```php
// app/Http/Resources/ProductResource.php
class ProductResource extends JsonResource
{
    public function toArray(Request $request): array
    {
        return [
            'id'    => $this->id,
            'name'  => $this->name,
            'price' => $this->price,
            'slug'  => $this->slug,
        ];
    }
}
```

---

### Validation Errors → 422 JSON

Laravel automatically returns 422 with `errors` object when validation fails:

```json
{
    "message": "The name field is required.",
    "errors": {
        "name": ["The name field is required."],
        "price": ["The price field must be a number."]
    }
}
```

---

### Authentication → Sanctum

```php
// app/Http/Controllers/Api/AuthController.php
public function login(Request $request): \Illuminate\Http\JsonResponse
{
    $credentials = $request->validate([
        'email'    => 'required|email',
        'password' => 'required',
    ]);

    if (!Auth::attempt($credentials)) {
        return response()->json(['message' => 'Invalid credentials'], 401);
    }

    $token = $request->user()->createToken('api-token')->plainTextToken;
    return response()->json(['token' => $token]);
}

public function logout(Request $request): \Illuminate\Http\JsonResponse
{
    $request->user()->currentAccessToken()->delete();
    return response()->json(['message' => 'Logged out']);
}
```

