### Cache Invalidation Strategy

| Action | What to Invalidate |
|--------|--------------------|
| Create product | `productKeys.list()` |
| Update product | `productKeys.detail(id)` + `productKeys.list()` |
| Delete product | `productKeys.list()` |
| Update user profile | `['user', id]` |

```ts
// Invalidate on update
onSuccess: (_, variables) => {
    qc.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: productKeys.list() });
    qc.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: productKeys.detail(variables.id) });
},
```

---

### Optimistic Updates (Optional — Better UX)

```ts
useMutation({
    mutationFn: updateProduct,
    onMutate: async (newProduct) => {
        // Cancel any in-flight queries
        await qc.cancelQueries({ queryKey: productKeys.detail(newProduct.id) });

        // Snapshot old value
        const previous = qc.getQueryData(productKeys.detail(newProduct.id));

        // Optimistically update cache
        qc.setQueryData(productKeys.detail(newProduct.id), newProduct);

        return { previous };
    },
    onError: (_, __, context) => {
        // Roll back on error
        qc.setQueryData(productKeys.detail(context!.previous!.id), context!.previous);
    },
    onSettled: (_, __, variables) => {
        qc.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: productKeys.detail(variables.id) });
    },
});
```

