## Migration Checklist

### Laravel API Setup
- [ ] Add `api-only` middleware or ensure all routes return JSON
- [ ] Create `API` controller folder and convert Blade controllers to return `JsonResource`
- [ ] Add `apiResource` routes in `routes/api.php`
- [ ] Install and configure Laravel Sanctum for token auth
- [ ] Configure CORS (`config/cors.php`) to allow Next.js origin
- [ ] Create API Resources for all models that will be exposed
- [ ] Ensure validation returns 422 with `errors` structure
- [ ] Add `auth:sanctum` middleware to protected routes

### Next.js Setup
- [ ] Create Next.js app with App Router: `npx create-next-app@latest --app`
- [ ] Install TanStack Query: `npm install @tanstack/react-query`
- [ ] Set up `QueryClientProvider` in root `layout.tsx`
- [ ] Create `lib/queryClient.ts` with `QueryClient` singleton
- [ ] Create `lib/api.ts` with base fetch wrapper (sets `Authorization` header)
- [ ] Create `lib/hooks/` for domain-specific query/mutation hooks
- [ ] Add `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` to `.env.local`
- [ ] Add `'use client'` to all interactive page/component files

### Feature Migration
- [ ] Map each Laravel web route to a Next.js `app/` route
- [ ] Convert each Livewire/Inertia controller to return JSON via `JsonResource`
- [ ] Replace Livewire `mount()` data loading with `useQuery()`
- [ ] Replace Livewire form actions / Inertia `useForm` with `useMutation()`
- [ ] Set up authentication flow (login → store token → use in `apiFetch`)
- [ ] Set up shared user state (either context or TanStack Query `useQuery(['user'])`)
- [ ] Handle 422 validation errors from `useMutation`'s `error` state
- [ ] Test all query invalidations after mutations
- [ ] Verify `staleTime` and `gcTime` are appropriate per query
- [ ] Test CORS — check browser network tab for CORS errors

